g.aria-label:
You try to toss it and catch it, play around with it, and notice soon enough that this coin is no ordinary coin,
It doesn’t show heads and tails with equal probability, in fact,
The coin has a bias!
This is likely the Rogue getting up to her mischief --- the coin is charmed. The probability of getting heads is some real number, p ∈ (0, 1), and that of getting tails is 1-p.
